    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1933-02-09T11:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1933-02-09T11:00:00-05:00" n="2"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d2">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">710.G/125: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in Argentina</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Bliss</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Buenos Aires</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1933-02-09T13:00:00-03:00"
                            >February 9, 1933—1 p.m.</date>
                        <lb/>[Received 4:52 p.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>17. Your 9, February 8, noon.<note n="3" xml:id="d2fn3">See footnote 1,
                        above.</note> Member of Chilean delegation at Mendoza conference tells me no
                    question was raised regarding postponement Pan American Conference, only
                    desirability of accord on subjects to be discussed. See paragraph 6 enclosure 1
                    my despatch No. 1957, February 3d.<note n="4" xml:id="d2fn4">Not printed.</note>
                    I understand no agreement yet reached regarding definite topics of the
                    program.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Bliss</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
